#featureless-space
(room *)
(name *) Endless Featureless Space
(look *)
    You are in an endless, featureless space, receding off to the distance in every
    direction. The only break from the monotony is a small circular table in front of you.

#player
(current player *)
(descr *)
    As undefined as the space you inhabit.
(* is #in #featureless-space)

#table 
(name *) circular table
(descr *)
    A medium sized table, circular, made of a milky-white, almost translucent, material. 
    (list objects #on *)
(supporter *)
(* is #in #featureless-space)

(global variable (confirmation value $))

#switch
(name *) red toggle switch
(switchable *)
(* is on)
(* is #on #table)
(descr *) A red toggle switch.
(prevent [switch off *])
    A pleasant voice announces "This switch deactivates the universe. Are you sure you want to proceed?"
    You intuit that you merely need to think your response.
    \(yes or no\)
    (space)
    (get key $Char)
    [You pressed: $Char]
    (now) (confirmation value $Char)
    (if) ($Char = @y)
    (then)
        (fail)
    (else)
        Oh, thank heavens!
    (endif)
(perform [switch off *])
    (game over { The light dims to blackness. })
